						<summary>

						<p>On the north base of the Karivaradarāja-perumāḻ temple.</p>						

						<p>This very much damaged inscription describes the king (name lost) as Parakēsarivarmaṉ and records the royal grant of land for a flower-garden, named after the king, for the temple of Emberumāṉ Kariyapirāṉ at [Kumaraṅga]bhīmach-chaturvēdimaṅgalam. </p>						

						</summary>
